==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Contredanse
<hw>Con"tre*danse`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>contredanse</ets> (fr. E. <er>Country-dance</er>). ]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>A dance in which the partners are arranged
face to face, or in opposite lines.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>The
quadrille.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Music)</fld> <def>A piece of music in the rhythm of
such a dance.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Contretemps</ent>⟦br⟧
\'d8
